  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n<img alt=\"The figure shows a dashed circle labeled with diameter D. A point is drawn in the center of the circle. Two small filled circles labeled M are drawn on the furthest left and right points on the circle. Arrows labeled point from each of these circles along the circle in the counterclockwise direction. \" src=\"/images/872865ef9dadbbd1b8919441254fadaf.png\" width=\"400\">\n<p>Two identical stars, a fixed distance <em>D</em> apart, revolve in a circle about their mutual center of mass, as shown above. Each star has a mass <em>M</em> and speed <em>V</em>. <em>G</em> is the universal gravitational constant. Which of the following is a correct relationship among these quantities?</p>",
